President Biden has declared a major disaster in Virginia due to severe winter storms that occurred from February 11 to February 13, 2021. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Kevin I. Snyder has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and warranted by damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.